# Modeling MasterControl's MX problem
## Statement of Business and Analytic Problems
The challenge MasterControl faces is in its conversion rate for the new Mx product line. Historically, with their well known Qx line, MasterControl has maintained a 19.7% conversion rate on their leads. Mx, however, only has a conversion rate of 12.7%. MasterControl would benefit from a customer profile made up of potential industries, manufacturing models, and contact titles they could use to optimize their outreach efforts. 
Analytically, this requires us to model the relationships between these key features and the conversion of their past Mx leads. We plan on using various modelling techniques, specifically Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and Gradient Boosted Trees to find these relationships. We also use the text-based latent dirichtlet analysis to find groups into which we can bin free-text field answers. 


